- peel and chop into fries
- soak in water and rinse a few times until water runs clear
- boil in water with salt (lots) and baking soda (a little) until just tender (i.e. doesn't snap), about 5 mins
- pat dry
- freeze / chill
- blanch (in oil) at 140°C stirring constantly
- freeze/chill again
- fry at 190°C until done
